general
=======
http://www.codeforamerica.org - landing page for united states
https://www.codefor.de - landing page for germany
http://guides.codeforaustralia.org/ - Brigade guides from Australia
http://codeforsanfrancisco.org/beta/ , http://codeforphilly.org - Templates for new Brigade sites
http://schoolofdata.org/handbook/ - detail and background theory to support the School of Data courses and challenges


social
======
http://www.reddit.com/r/civichackers - civic hacking subreddit
https://lists.okfn.org/mailman/listinfo - open knowledge foundation mailing list overview
https://hackpad.com/Code-for-All-Tools-and-Tactics-1LbiMvniTDc - protocoll hackpad while meetup July 13, 2014 in Berlin
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qNmFNxtdIokBfh_9JcYvrWKSRCAgcqSqeaX4LGm8a-0/edit#heading=h.hylgo2d28584 - (german only) Protokoll vom 12/13 July CodeFor.de Lab-Treffen in Berlin
https://pad.okfn.org/p/Tools_tools_and_more_tools -  Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, pad of the session "Tools tools and more tools"


tools
=====
https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/digital-skills-in-the-civil-service/an-introductory-guide-to-open-internet-tools-for-civil-servants - Tool guide for gov employees
http://civicpatterns.org/ - Patterns to use while building civic tech
https://slack.com - Great chat service for your team. - used by the CodeForAmerica (Kansas?)
https://cartodb.com/ - Powerful mapping service - via. via: Open Knowledge Festival Berlin and talk @csvConf2014
https://plot.ly - online analytics and data visualization tool (partner of csvConf.com) (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plotly)
http://lab.hakim.se/reveal-js - reveal.js - A framework for easily creating beautiful presentations using HTML. 
https://source.opennews.org/en-US/ - Discussions on journalism tech
https://morph.io/ - A collection of scrapers
http://www.nltk.org - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_Language_Toolkit - language processing tool (used: http://github.com/codeformuenster/wahlprogramm-matrix)
http://www.alchemyapi.com - for named entitz extraction, natural language processing - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
https://www.import.io - website that extracting tables - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
https://www.kimonolabs.com - turn websites into structured APIs from your browser,  no more scraping - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
https://github.com/propublica/upton - a web scraping framework - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
https://developers.google.com/fusiontables/ - like excel, georeferencing options, visualise on map, can run sql - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
http://openrefine.org - transform data in a couple of steps and the actions are written in javascript so you can use it afterwards - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
http://vis.stanford.edu/wrangler - alternative to open refine - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
http://www.pentaho.de - business annylize and intelligence, has an open source version.  kettle - extract, transform - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
https://www.gnu.org/software/pspp - PSPP - open source version of SPSS - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
http://tapor.ca - Library of text analysis tools. Visualisation. Mostly used by academics - via: Open Knowledge Festival, Berlin, session "Tools tools and more tools"
